From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman: per-key FQ enqueue-AD + silicon-truth CC key layout
 (M3-3b close-out)

Closes the last M3-3b gap (spec sec 5.4): a CC key can now steer a
specific 5-tuple to a SPECIFIC target frame queue.  The 0107 lifecycle
validation (2026-06-10) proved install/graft/traffic/detach on silicon
but left two known deficiencies in the 0098 static installer; this patch
fixes both.

1. Real hardware enqueue-AD (the headline item)
-----------------------------------------------
0098's cc_write_leaf_ad() wrote a SOFT encoding (word0 =
qband<<16|hm<<8|type - "the dpaa flavor layer owns the qband->FQID
map"), NOT the RM 8.7.4.3 hardware AD, so matched frames completed the
CC walk and fell through to normal scheme dispatch.  The leaf encoder
now emits the ask20-HW-PROVEN encoding (PR14z20/PR14z22 silicon
captures, 24M+ frames CC-matched and silicon-forwarded) whenever a
target FQID is supplied:

  word0 (0x0) = fqid & 0x00ffffff      (target frame queue)
  word1 (0x4) = 0                      (no policer pass)
  word2 (0x8) = RESULT_CF [| NADEN]    (enqueue; walk HMTD first when
                                        an HM node is chained)
  word3 (0xc) = hm_handle              (HMTD MURAM offset; 0 = none)

A silicon HIT on such a row enqueues the frame directly to the target
FQ, bypassing the KeyGen hash dispatch.  fqid == 0 keeps the
DUT-validated soft fall-through encoding byte-identical (and remains
the default), so existing behaviour is unchanged unless a caller
explicitly opts in.  The miss slot uses the same selector via the new
miss_fqid (0 = miss traffic stays on the port's RSS path).

New plumbing: u32 target_fqid in struct fman_pcd_cc_hw_key and struct
fman_cc_key, u32 miss_fqid in struct fman_pcd_cc_hw_spec and struct
fman_cc_static_tree, passthrough in dpaa_cc_key_to_hw() /
fman_cc_tree_install().  Resolving target_qband -> FQID stays the dpaa
flavor layer's job (per the 0098 design note); an explicit FQID is
authoritative.

2. Silicon-truth match-key layout (required for a HIT to ever occur)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Under the 0106 KGSE_CCBS graft model the CC walker compares the
KeyGen-EXTRACTED composite - the bytes the port's existing RSS scheme
emits per its KGSE_EKFC (0x00180206 = IPSRC1|IPDST1|IPSEC_SPI|L4PSRC|
L4PDST), i.e. [SIP(4)|DIP(4)|SPI(4)=0|SPORT(2)|DPORT(2)] = 16 bytes.
This was DUT-proven on ask20 (PR14z14 silicon truth; PR14z22 DROP-miss
diagnostic: 24M frames matched with this layout).  0098's composite
(ethertype/proto/flags/IP/ports) could NEVER match because the walker
does not re-extract.  cc_pack_key() now emits the silicon-truth layout.
Documented limitations (loud, not silent): ETHERTYPE/PROTO cannot
participate (not in the KG composite); IPv6 keys are rejected with
-ENOTSUPP at install; SPI is exact-matched as zero (plain-IP shape).

3. Harness extension
--------------------
The 0107 cc_test debugfs node gains an optional trailing argument:

  install <hwport> <qband> <proto> <src_ip> <dst_ip> <dport> [fqid-hex]

A non-zero fqid (e.g. 0x6e = eth3's RX-default FQ from the silicon
captures) arms the real per-key enqueue-AD for DUT validation: send a
matching flow, confirm delivery via the target FQ's counters, then
clear and confirm fall-through is restored.

Native arm64 compile of drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/{fman,dpaa}/
with LOCALVERSION=-vyos: 0 warnings / 0 errors.

Spec sec 5.4; AD encoding per LS1046A RM 8.7.4.3 Table 8-119, cross-ref
SDK fm_cc.c GetAdOfTypeResult()/NextStepAd().

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
index e867fa5..8fcc571 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c
@@ -244,6 +244,7 @@ hw->present |= FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_DST_PORT;
 }
 
 hw->target_qband = k->target_qband;
+hw->target_fqid = k->target_fqid;
 hw->hm_handle = k->hm_handle;
 }
 
@@ -287,6 +288,7 @@ return -ENOMEM;
 
 hw->num_keys = spec->num_keys;
 hw->miss_qband = spec->miss_qband;
+hw->miss_fqid = spec->miss_fqid;
 for (i = 0; i < spec->num_keys; i++)
 dpaa_cc_key_to_hw(&spec->keys[i], &hw->keys[i]);
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
index eb2aa1a..4fcc610 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h
@@ -141,8 +141,17 @@ void fman_cc_tree_destroy(struct fman *fm, u8 port_id);
  * @src_ip_mask:  prefix-style mask for src_ip (host-endian); 0 = any
  * @dst_ip_mask:  prefix-style mask for dst_ip (host-endian); 0 = any
  * @target_qband: qband [0 .. xsk_max_qbands-1] to steer matching frames
+ * @target_fqid:  explicit target frame-queue id for matching frames.
+ *                Non-zero = the leaf AD is the REAL RM 8.7.4.3 hardware
+ *                enqueue-AD: a silicon HIT enqueues directly to this FQ
+ *                (per-key FQ steering).  0 = soft fall-through (the frame
+ *                proceeds to the normal RSS scheme dispatch).  When 0 and
+ *                a consumer wants qband steering it must resolve
+ *                target_qband -> FQID itself (the dpaa flavor layer owns
+ *                that map) and set this field.
  * @hm_handle:    HM node handle to chain after match (0 = no HM); the
- *                value returned by fman_hm_node_install() per spec sec 5.5
+ *                value returned by fman_hm_node_install() per spec sec 5.5.
+ *                Honoured only with a non-zero @target_fqid.
  * @is_ipv6:      when true, match src_ip6/dst_ip6 instead of src_ip/dst_ip
  *
  * A field is matched iff it (or its mask) is non-zero. The productive
@@ -163,6 +172,7 @@ struct fman_cc_key {
 	u16 src_port;
 	u16 dst_port;
 	u16 target_qband;
+	u32 target_fqid;
 	u32 hm_handle;
 };
 
@@ -171,6 +181,10 @@ struct fman_cc_key {
  * @num_keys: number of valid entries in @keys
  * @miss_qband: qband for frames matching no key (the tree's miss action);
  *              default 0 maps to the existing RSS-hash default path
+ * @miss_fqid: explicit FQID for frames matching no key; non-zero = the
+ *             miss slot carries a hardware enqueue-AD (steers ALL
+ *             non-matching traffic - use deliberately), 0 = miss traffic
+ *             stays on the existing RSS-hash path (the default)
  * @keys: the key array, evaluated in order; first match wins
  *
  * Passed to fman_cc_tree_install() for the static (default/vpp) lifecycle.
@@ -183,6 +197,7 @@ struct fman_cc_key {
 struct fman_cc_static_tree {
 	u16 num_keys;
 	u16 miss_qband;
+	u32 miss_fqid;
 	struct fman_cc_key keys[FMAN_CC_MAX_STATIC_KEYS];
 };
 
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
index 9ac649c..fb8dd6f 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc.c
@@ -71,9 +71,11 @@
  *                     entries are zero = no-match.  gen_pool min_alloc_order
  *                     = 8 satisfies the 256-byte alignment naturally.
  * CC_AD_ENTRY_SIZE  : bytes per action descriptor.
- * CC_KEY_SIZE       : our fixed extracted-key width.  We extract a canonical
- *                     16-byte composite (ethertype/proto/IP/ports) packed
- *                     big-endian; the per-key match record is key+mask =
+ * CC_KEY_SIZE       : the fixed compared-key width.  Under the KGSE_CCBS
+ *                     graft model the silicon compares the KeyGen-EXTRACTED
+ *                     composite (the port scheme's EKFC bytes:
+ *                     [SIP|DIP|SPI|SPORT|DPORT] = 16 bytes, see
+ *                     cc_pack_key()); the per-key match record is key+mask =
  *                     2 * CC_KEY_SIZE bytes.  RM 8.7.4.2 caps extract.size at
  *                     1..56; 16 is comfortably within range.
  */
@@ -84,6 +86,39 @@
 /* CONT_LOOKUP action-descriptor words (RM 8.7.4.1). */
 #define CC_AD_W2_CONT_LOOKUP	0x40000000u
 
+/*
+ * Leaf (result) action-descriptor field layout — RM 8.7.4.3 Table 8-119.
+ *
+ * The 16-byte MURAM-resident AD record is four big-endian 32-bit words:
+ *
+ *   0x0  u32 fqid          - egress FQID for RESULT_* actions (24-bit)
+ *   0x4  u32 plcr_profile  - policer profile id + enable bits
+ *   0x8  u32 nia           - type[31:30] | flags[29:4] | opcode[3:0]
+ *   0xc  u32 res           - reserved / HMTD pointer when NADEN is set
+ *
+ * type bits nia[31:30]: 00 = RESULT_CONTRL_FLOW (enqueue to fqid),
+ * 01 = CONT_LOOKUP (next CC node), 10 = RESULT_DATA_FLOW, 11 = BYPASS
+ * (drop / discard).  NADEN in nia[29] redirects the silicon walker
+ * through the 16-byte HMTD at @res before enqueueing to @fqid (the
+ * CC->HM chain, spec sec 5.4 order Parser->CC->HM->QMan).
+ *
+ * HW-PROVEN (ask20 silicon captures PR14z20/PR14z22, 2026-05-23): 24M+
+ * frames were CC-matched and silicon-forwarded through exactly this
+ * encoding (RESULT_CF + fqid for plain forward; RESULT_CF | NADEN +
+ * fqid + res=HMTD for the manip-chained forward) under the KGSE_CCBS
+ * graft model that board patch 0106 wires.  Cross-ref SDK fm_cc.c
+ * GetAdOfTypeResult() / NextStepAd().
+ */
+#define CC_AD_OFF_FQID		0x0
+#define CC_AD_OFF_PLCR		0x4
+#define CC_AD_OFF_NIA		0x8
+#define CC_AD_OFF_RES		0xc
+
+#define CC_AD_NIA_TYPE_RESULT_CF	0x00000000u	/* enqueue to fqid */
+#define CC_AD_NIA_TYPE_BYPASS		0xc0000000u	/* drop / discard  */
+#define CC_AD_NIA_NADEN			0x20000000u	/* walk HMTD @res  */
+#define CC_AD_FQID_MASK			0x00ffffffu	/* FQIDs are 24-bit */
+
 /**
  * struct fman_pcd_cc_tree - one port's static CC tree handle (private).
  * @node:          anchor on pcd->cc_trees (protected by pcd->lock)
@@ -132,23 +167,40 @@ static struct fman_pcd_cc_tree *cc_find_locked(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id)
 }
 
 /*
- * Pack one normalised key into a CC_KEY_SIZE-byte big-endian composite +
- * its mask, written into the match record at row @idx.  The composite layout
- * is fixed (it mirrors the parser extract the install programs):
+ * Pack one normalised key into the CC_KEY_SIZE-byte composite the silicon
+ * compares, plus its mask, written into the match record at row @idx.
+ *
+ * SILICON-TRUTH LAYOUT (ask20 PR14z14/PR14z22, DUT-proven 2026-05-23):
+ * under the KGSE_CCBS graft model (board patch 0106) the CC walker
+ * compares the KeyGen-EXTRACTED composite, i.e. the bytes the port's
+ * existing RSS scheme emits per its KGSE_EKFC.  The mainline default
+ * scheme's EKFC is 0x00180206 = IPSRC1 | IPDST1 | IPSEC_SPI | L4PSRC |
+ * L4PDST, which extracts exactly 16 bytes:
+ *
+ *   bytes 0..3   IPv4 src (network order)
+ *   bytes 4..7   IPv4 dst (network order)
+ *   bytes 8..11  IPsec SPI (0x00000000 for plain IP/TCP/UDP frames)
+ *   bytes 12..13 L4 src port (network order)
+ *   bytes 14..15 L4 dst port (network order)
+ *
+ * The DROP-miss diagnostic (ask20 patch 0053) proved silicon HITs with
+ * this exact layout: 24M frames matched and forwarded with miss=DROP and
+ * throughput unchanged.  The previous 0098 composite
+ * (ethertype/proto/flags/IP/ports) could NEVER match because the walker
+ * does not re-extract — it compares the KG-emitted bytes.
  *
- *   bytes 0..1   ethertype (BE)
- *   byte  2      proto
- *   byte  3      flags (bit0 = is_ipv6)
- *   bytes 4..7   IPv4 src (BE)   [or first 4 of IPv6 src for v6]
- *   bytes 8..11  IPv4 dst (BE)   [or first 4 of IPv6 dst for v6]
- *   bytes 12..13 L4 src port (BE)
- *   bytes 14..15 L4 dst port (BE)
+ * Consequences (documented limitations, not silent):
+ *  - ETHERTYPE / PROTO cannot participate: the KG composite carries
+ *    neither.  A TCP and a UDP flow with identical addresses+ports are
+ *    indistinguishable to this tree.  The presence flags are accepted
+ *    (the dpaa-side translator sets them) but do not contribute bytes.
+ *  - IPv6 keys cannot match a v4-shaped 16-byte composite;
+ *    fman_pcd_cc_static_install() rejects them with -ENOTSUPP.
+ *  - The SPI field is exact-matched as zero (the HW-proven shape for
+ *    plain IP traffic); ESP flows are out of scope for this tree.
  *
- * The mask row mirrors the same layout: 0xff for participating bytes, 0x00
- * for wildcard.  This is sufficient for the IPv4 5-tuple shape the dpaa1
- * default/vpp consumers use; IPv6 full-address matching is a follow-up that
- * widens CC_KEY_SIZE (handled loudly: an IPv6 key still matches its first 4
- * address bytes here, which the dpaa-side translator flags).
+ * The mask row mirrors the layout: 0xff for participating bytes, 0x00
+ * for wildcard.
  */
 static void cc_pack_key(void __iomem *match, u16 idx,
 			const struct fman_pcd_cc_hw_key *k)
@@ -160,34 +212,16 @@ static void cc_pack_key(void __iomem *match, u16 idx,
 	memset(key, 0, sizeof(key));
 	memset(msk, 0, sizeof(msk));
 
-	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_ETHERTYPE) {
-		key[0] = (u8)(k->ethertype_be & 0xff);
-		key[1] = (u8)(k->ethertype_be >> 8);
-		msk[0] = msk[1] = 0xff;
-	}
-	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_PROTO) {
-		key[2] = k->proto;
-		msk[2] = 0xff;
-	}
-	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_IPV6)
-		key[3] |= 0x01;
-	/* flags byte is structural, always exact-matched */
-	msk[3] = 0xff;
-
 	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_SRC_IP) {
-		if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_IPV6)
-			memcpy(&key[4], &k->src_ip6[0], 4);
-		else
-			memcpy(&key[4], &k->src_ip_be, 4);
-		msk[4] = msk[5] = msk[6] = msk[7] = 0xff;
+		memcpy(&key[0], &k->src_ip_be, 4);
+		msk[0] = msk[1] = msk[2] = msk[3] = 0xff;
 	}
 	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_DST_IP) {
-		if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_IPV6)
-			memcpy(&key[8], &k->dst_ip6[0], 4);
-		else
-			memcpy(&key[8], &k->dst_ip_be, 4);
-		msk[8] = msk[9] = msk[10] = msk[11] = 0xff;
+		memcpy(&key[4], &k->dst_ip_be, 4);
+		msk[4] = msk[5] = msk[6] = msk[7] = 0xff;
 	}
+	/* bytes 8..11: IPsec SPI — exact-match zero (HW-proven shape). */
+	msk[8] = msk[9] = msk[10] = msk[11] = 0xff;
 	if (k->present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_SRC_PORT) {
 		key[12] = (u8)(k->src_port_be & 0xff);
 		key[13] = (u8)(k->src_port_be >> 8);
@@ -206,33 +240,56 @@ static void cc_pack_key(void __iomem *match, u16 idx,
 }
 
 /*
- * Encode one CONT_LOOKUP action descriptor (RM 8.7.4.3) at AD row @idx.
- * For a matching key we steer to the target RX FQ derived from the qband;
- * the dpaa flavor layer owns the qband->FQID map, so here we encode the
- * qband directly into the AD's result field and let the walker's FQID base
- * register resolve it.  hm_handle, when non-zero, is encoded into the NIA
- * (next-invoked-action) HMTD offset so the CC->HM chain (spec sec 5.4 order
- * Parser->CC->HM->QMan) is honoured.
+ * Encode one leaf (result) action descriptor (RM 8.7.4.3) at AD row @idx.
  *
- * AD word layout we emit for a leaf result entry:
- *   word0 = (qband << 16) | (hm_present << 8) | type
- *   word1 = hm_handle (HMTD MURAM offset; 0 when no HM)
- *   word2 = 0
- *   word3 = 0
- * where type 0x1 = "result / enqueue".  This is the leaf form; the
- * group-table[0] entry below is the CONT_LOOKUP that points the walker at
- * this AD table.
+ * Two regimes, selected by @fqid:
+ *
+ * @fqid != 0 — the REAL hardware enqueue-AD (per-key FQ steering):
+ *   word0 (0x0) = fqid & CC_AD_FQID_MASK   (target frame queue)
+ *   word1 (0x4) = 0                        (no policer pass)
+ *   word2 (0x8) = RESULT_CF [| NADEN]      (enqueue; walk HMTD first
+ *                                           when @hm chains an HM node)
+ *   word3 (0xc) = hm                       (HMTD MURAM offset; 0 = none)
+ *   A silicon CC HIT on this row enqueues the frame directly to @fqid,
+ *   bypassing the KeyGen scheme's hash dispatch entirely.  This is the
+ *   ask20-HW-proven encoding (24M+ frames silicon-forwarded, PR14z22).
+ *
+ * @fqid == 0 — graceful fall-through (DUT-validated 2026-06-10): the
+ *   legacy soft encoding whose word0 is a reserved-shape token, NOT a
+ *   live FQID; the walk completes and the frame proceeds to the normal
+ *   scheme dispatch (hashed RX FQs).  Kept byte-identical to the 0098
+ *   encoding the 0107 lifecycle validation ran against:
+ *   word0 = (qband << 16) | (hm_present << 8) | 0x1, word1 = hm,
+ *   word2 = word3 = 0.  An HM chain cannot be honoured in this regime
+ *   (NADEN needs a target FQID for the post-manip enqueue).
+ *
+ * The miss slot (last AD row) uses the same encoder: a non-zero
+ * @fqid there steers every non-matching frame, fqid 0 leaves miss
+ * traffic on the port's existing RSS path.
  */
-static void cc_write_leaf_ad(void __iomem *ad, u16 idx, u16 qband, u32 hm)
+static void cc_write_leaf_ad(void __iomem *ad, u16 idx, u32 fqid,
+			     u16 qband, u32 hm)
 {
 	u32 __iomem *w = (u32 __iomem *)((u8 __force *)ad +
 					 (size_t)idx * CC_AD_ENTRY_SIZE);
-	u32 w0 = ((u32)qband << 16) | ((hm ? 1u : 0u) << 8) | 0x1u;
 
-	iowrite32be(w0, &w[0]);
-	iowrite32be(hm, &w[1]);
-	iowrite32be(0, &w[2]);
-	iowrite32be(0, &w[3]);
+	if (fqid) {
+		u32 nia = CC_AD_NIA_TYPE_RESULT_CF;
+
+		if (hm)
+			nia |= CC_AD_NIA_NADEN;
+		iowrite32be(fqid & CC_AD_FQID_MASK, &w[0]);
+		iowrite32be(0, &w[1]);
+		iowrite32be(nia, &w[2]);
+		iowrite32be(hm, &w[3]);
+	} else {
+		u32 w0 = ((u32)qband << 16) | ((hm ? 1u : 0u) << 8) | 0x1u;
+
+		iowrite32be(w0, &w[0]);
+		iowrite32be(hm, &w[1]);
+		iowrite32be(0, &w[2]);
+		iowrite32be(0, &w[3]);
+	}
 }
 
 /*
@@ -283,6 +340,14 @@ int fman_pcd_cc_static_install(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id,
 		return -EINVAL;
 	if (hw->num_keys > FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_MAX_KEYS)
 		return -EINVAL;
+	/*
+	 * IPv6 keys cannot match the v4-shaped 16-byte KG-emitted composite
+	 * this tree compares (see cc_pack_key()); reject loudly rather than
+	 * install a key that can never hit.
+	 */
+	for (i = 0; i < hw->num_keys; i++)
+		if (hw->keys[i].present & FMAN_PCD_CC_HW_F_IPV6)
+			return -ENOTSUPP;
 
 	muram = fman_get_muram(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd));
 	if (!muram)
@@ -336,11 +401,15 @@ int fman_pcd_cc_static_install(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 port_id,
 	/* Encode each key's match record + leaf result AD. */
 	for (i = 0; i < hw->num_keys; i++) {
 		cc_pack_key(t->match, i, &hw->keys[i]);
-		cc_write_leaf_ad(t->ad, i, hw->keys[i].target_qband,
+		cc_write_leaf_ad(t->ad, i, hw->keys[i].target_fqid,
+				 hw->keys[i].target_qband,
 				 hw->keys[i].hm_handle);
 	}
-	/* Miss slot (last row): steer to miss_qband, no HM. */
-	cc_write_leaf_ad(t->ad, hw->num_keys, hw->miss_qband, 0);
+	/*
+	 * Miss slot (last row): a non-zero miss_fqid steers all non-matching
+	 * frames to that FQ; 0 leaves miss traffic on the existing RSS path.
+	 */
+	cc_write_leaf_ad(t->ad, hw->num_keys, hw->miss_fqid, hw->miss_qband, 0);
 
 	/* Point the walker at the tables via the group-table[0] CONT_LOOKUP. */
 	cc_write_group0(t);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc_test.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc_test.c
index d9f4134..c9240cf 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc_test.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_cc_test.c
@@ -11,10 +11,14 @@
  *   /sys/kernel/debug/fman_pcd/<N>/cc_test
  *
  * Write commands (drives the EXACT 0106 productive sequence):
- *   install <hwport> <qband> <proto> <src_ip> <dst_ip> <dport>
+ *   install <hwport> <qband> <proto> <src_ip> <dst_ip> <dport> [fqid-hex]
  *       -> fman_pcd_cc_static_install() (one IPv4 exact-match key)
  *       -> fman_pcd_cc_static_get_base()
  *       -> fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc()   (the KGSE_CCBS graft)
+ *       The optional trailing fqid (hex, e.g. 0x6e) arms the REAL
+ *       per-key hardware enqueue-AD: a silicon HIT enqueues matching
+ *       frames directly to that FQ.  Omitted or 0 = the soft
+ *       fall-through leaf (lifecycle validation only).
  *   clear <hwport>
  *       -> fman_pcd_kg_port_detach_cc()
  *       -> fman_pcd_cc_static_destroy()
@@ -63,13 +67,14 @@ static int cc_test_install(struct fman_pcd *pcd, const char *args)
